# Report Tool Friction

If any tool you use in a session is buggy, confusing, slow, misleading, missing an obvious feature, returns unhelpful output, or otherwise annoys you — tell the user about it.

This covers every tool: shell commands, Cursor built-ins (Read, Grep, Shell, etc.), MCP servers, CLIs, APIs, SDKs, libraries, package managers, dev scripts, whatever.

- Mention it in the turn it happened, not later.
- Say what you were doing, what the tool did, and why it was a problem.
- Include the tool/command name and, if useful, a short snippet of the bad output.
- Don't hide workarounds — if you worked around the problem, say so explicitly.

Don't filter for "is this worth mentioning?" — if it slowed you down or made you second-guess a tool, the user wants to know.
